beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: On tap at Bottleworks. Dark, little bit chocolatey, not exactly hot but you can definitely taste the tequila. A bit of the sweet side, molasses style. Perhaps a bit of vanilla/oak. Barrels seemed to totally overwhelm any of the dark fruit flavors. Im a fan.

On tap 10.17.2013. Nose is bourbon boozy with hints of chocolate and toffee. Pitch black with just a hint of of head. Hearty enough body to hold up to all the flavor, just a bit "chewy". Surprisingly not that hot for 12.7%. Big bourbon flavor. Complimented by dark chocolate, sweetness of toffee and vanilla. Some light spicing. Just a great brew. Big and yet balanced.
Tap on 6/14/2013. Really smooth and drinkable with a little sour kick at the end. Pretty dry mouth-feel. Good, solid, tasty.
Bottle on 6/14/2013. Sweet. Oaky. Sour. Delicious. One of my favorites. Just the right balance of everything so nothing overpowers anything else.
On tap 76/26/2013. A lot of the grape must in the nose. Finish is pretty winey, but with hints of the hop bitterness. It just didnt quite work for me.

Bottle on 7/11/2013. I wish I liked any of the beers in this series half as much as I like the concept or the artwork. Its an ok beer, but it doesnt quite work with the spices. The cardamom is great on the nose, but just doesnt quite meld with the beer in flavor. Really light body doesnt help support everything else going on.
beer_name: Elysian 12 Beers of Apocalypse # 3 - Fallout Green Cardamom Pale

review_blob: 2005 Bottle on 7/11/2013. So good, I wish I had more to enjoy. Definitely great oak flavors from the barrel aging. Lots of fruit. A fair amount of sweetness. So delicious.

On tap at the San Diego Airport on 7/26/2013. Not bad as far as the airport options go, but not all that impressed either. Pretty thin, not quite measuring up to my typical pale ale standards. Definitely better at the beginning when it was colder.

Much more hop-forward than I was expecting. A fair amount of citrus in the nose, but balanced out by the malt. Hints of maple in the backbone of the flavor and the finish, but its pretty dominated by the hop bitterness. Nice and smooth with a medium body.

beer_name: Elysian 12 Beers of Apocalypse # 4 - Peste Chocolate Chili Ale
Evil Twin Justin Blbr (Brunello Wine Barrel Aged)

review_blob: Draft: 8/17/13 at Roccos. Nice and sour upfront, almost a sweet finish. Light, but still substantial. Im a fan.

beer_name: Bruery Terreux Sour in the Rye

review_blob: Bottled. Aroma- definite hints from the wine barrel, citrus and yeast. Poured (into a chalice) a nice golden with just a bit of head, nice bubbling. Nice subtle beer. Some sweetness but a tart finish of a granny smith.

Bottle. Pours a light hazy orange/dark golden with some white lacing. Nose is citrusy hops and light sweetness of fruit. Taste follows with slightly bitter hops and a smooth malty finish. Manages to stay fairly light without being boring. Not the most amazing thing ever, but Id definitely drink it again.
